                "html": `<h1>Week 6: The Box Model (Padding, Border, & Margin)</h1>
    <p>Today we learn that every HTML element is actually a box! We'll control spacing with padding, borders, and margins.</p>

    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>ğŸ–¼ï¸ Analogy: The Framed Photo</b><br />

        â€¢ <strong>Content</strong> â†’ The photo itself<br />
        â€¢ <strong>Padding</strong> â†’ White space/matting inside the frame<br />
        â€¢ <strong>Border</strong> â†’ The picture frame<br />
        â€¢ <strong>Margin</strong> â†’ Space between this frame and the next one on the wall<br />
        â€¢ <strong>Every element on a webpage is a framed picture!</strong>
    </div>

    <h3>ğŸ“¦ What is the Box Model?</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
        <p>The CSS Box Model describes the rectangular boxes generated for elements. Each box has:</p>

        <div style="position: relative; height: 200px; margin: 30px auto; width: 400px;">
            <!-- Margin -->
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; border: 2px dashed #4A90E2; padding: 20px;">
                <div style="text-align: center; color: #4A90E2; font-weight: bold;">Margin</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Border -->
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 20px; left: 20px; right: 20px; bottom: 20px; border: 10px solid #F5A623; padding: 20px;">
                <div style="text-align: center; color: #F5A623; font-weight: bold;">Border</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Padding -->
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 50px; left: 50px; right: 50px; bottom: 50px; background: rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.3); padding: 20px;">
                <div style="text-align: center; color: #4ECDC4; font-weight: bold;">Padding</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Content -->
