                "html": `<h1>Week 10: Functions (The Action Button)</h1>
    <p><b>Goal:</b> Learn how to package code into reusable blocks called functions that make things happen when you click!</p>

    <div class=\"analogy-box\" style=\"background-color: #f0f7ff; border-left: 5px solid #4299e1; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 8px;\">
        <h3>ğŸ• Analogy: The Pizza Delivery Service</h3>
        <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: center; margin-top: 10px;\">
            <div style=\"flex: 1; text-align: center; padding: 10px;\">
                <div style=\"font-size: 3em;\">ğŸ“</div>
                <b>1. You Call</b><br>
                <code>deliverPizza()</code>
            </div>
            <div style=\"flex: 1; text-align: center; padding: 10px;\">
                <div style=\"font-size: 3em;\">ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ³</div>
                <b>2. Kitchen Works</b><br>
                <code>function deliverPizza() { ... }</code>
            </div>
            <div style=\"flex: 1; text-align: center; padding: 10px;\">
                <div style=\"font-size: 3em;\">ğŸ•</div>
                <b>3. Pizza Arrives</b><br>
                <code>Hot pizza delivered!</code>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p><i>A function is like a pizza kitchen. You don't need to know how to make dough or turn on the oven. You just call the function and it does the work!</i></p>
    </div>

    <h2>Part 1: Building Your First Function</h2>
    
    <div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;\">
        <div style=\"background: #f7fafc; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e0;\">
            <h4>ğŸ”§ Function Anatomy</h4>
            <pre style=\"background: #2d3748; color: #fff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;\"><code>// FUNCTION DECLARATION
function functionName() {
    // Code that runs when function is called
    console.log("Function activated!");
}

// FUNCTION CALL (Run the function)
functionName(); // This triggers the code inside</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div style=\"background: #f0fff4; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #9ae6b4;\">
            <h4>ğŸ® Real Example: Game Power-up</h4>
            <pre style=\"background: #2d3748; color: #fff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;\"><code>let score = 0;
let lives = 3;

function collectCoin() {
    score = score + 100;
    console.log("+100 points! Total: " + score);
}

function loseLife() {
    lives = lives - 1;
    console.log("Ouch! Lives left: " + lives);
}

// Use the functions
collectCoin(); // Score becomes 100
collectCoin(); // Score becomes 200
loseLife();    // Lives becomes 2</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Part 2: Parameters - The Function's "Options Menu"</h2>
